5. Stripping and [RuntimeInitializeOnLoadMethod]

Technically:

- Unity can strip methods marked with [RuntimeInitializeOnLoadMethod] under High managed stripping if:
  - The containing type/assembly is otherwise unused and not preserved.
- Your link.xml preserving the Chorewars.Bootstrap namespace is a good move.

Safer pattern:

- In link.xml, preserve:
  - The specific types that contain RuntimeInitializeOnLoadMethod methods.
  - Any XR bootstrap types that are only referenced via attributes or reflection.

Example:

`xml
<linker>
  <assembly fullname="Assembly-CSharp">
    <type fullname="Chorewars.Bootstrap.QuestXrRigBootstrap" preserve="all" />
    <type fullname="Chorewars.Bootstrap.BootstrapSceneRouter" preserve="all" />
  </assembly>
</linker>
`

This is more explicit and robust than preserving entire namespaces if you want to keep stripping aggressive.

